<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-04-10T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-04-10T15:00:00-05:00" n="496" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d496">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/2342: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morales</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-04-10T14:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">April 10,
                                        1922—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 8
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>41. Referring to the Department’s telegram of April 8, 4 p.m. The
                            President is of the opinion that warship at Amapala is indispensable at
                            this time on account of seriousness of political situation in Salvador,
                            Nicaragua and Honduras.</p>
                        <p>Revolutionists on Salvadorean frontier very quiet but Government looking
                            for further attack from them. Ferrara left vicinity of Esperanza and is
                            now located near Gracias.</p>
                        <p>General Leiva was captured by Salvadorean forces and will be
                            reconcentrated.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Morales</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>